    <h2>LG Appliances We Repair</h2>

    <h3>LG Dryer Repair</h3>
    <p>Electric, gas, stackable, and LG ThinQ smart dryers. Common repairs: heating element replacement, drum roller replacement, thermal fuse, gas valve coils, igniter, motor, and control board. We carry OEM parts for the full DLGX, DLEX, DLE, and DLG lineup. Most LG dryer repairs are resolved same-day.</p>

    <h3>LG Washer Repair</h3>
    <p>Front-load and top-load LG washers including TurboWash and ThinQ models. Common issues: OE error (drainage failure), LE error (motor), UE error (unbalanced), door lock failure, drain pump, drum bearing, and door boot seal. We diagnose the root cause — not just clear the error code.</p>

    <h3>LG Refrigerator Repair</h3>
    <p>French door, side-by-side, and bottom-freezer LG refrigerators. Linear compressor failures, ice maker problems, cooling fan motors, and defrost system issues are the most common calls we receive. We carry linear compressor parts for the most affected LG models.</p>

    <h3>LG Range &amp; Oven Repair</h3>
    <p>Gas and electric LG ranges, wall ovens, and slide-in models. Igniter failures, bake element replacement, convection fan, and control board issues. We service LG Studio and LG ProBake Convection models.</p>

    <h3>LG Dishwasher Repair</h3>
    <p>Drainage pump failures, spray arm blockages, door latch issues, and AE error (water leak). We service all LG dishwasher models including QuadWash and TrueSteam lines.</p>

    <h2>Why Customers in LA and Orange County Choose Us</h2>

    <h3>Arrival in 1–1.5 Hours</h3>
    <p>We have technicians stationed across the greater Los Angeles area and Orange County. When you call, dispatch routes the nearest available technician to your location. Most customers see a technician at their door within 90 minutes.</p>

    <h3>$65 Diagnostic — Waived with Repair</h3>
    <p>Our technician arrives, runs a complete diagnostic, identifies the exact part that failed, and gives you a firm quote for the full repair. If you approve, the $65 is waived and you pay only the repair cost. No hidden fees.</p>

    <h3>OEM Parts Only</h3>
    <p>We stock genuine LG OEM parts in our service vans — never aftermarket substitutes. OEM parts maintain your manufacturer warranty, fit precisely, and last significantly longer than generic alternatives.</p>

    <h3>Three-Tier Warranty</h3>
    <p>Every repair is warranted on parts, on labor, and with a return visit guarantee. If the same problem recurs after our repair, we come back and fix it at no charge.</p>

    <h2>Service Area</h2>

    <p><strong>Los Angeles County:</strong> West Hollywood, Hollywood, Koreatown, Pasadena, Burbank, Glendale, Santa Monica, Culver City, Long Beach, Torrance, Manhattan Beach, Alhambra, Arcadia, Silver Lake, and all surrounding areas.</p>
    <p><strong>Orange County:</strong> Irvine, Anaheim, Santa Ana, Huntington Beach, Garden Grove, Fullerton, Costa Mesa, Newport Beach, Mission Viejo, and more.</p>
    <p><strong>Ventura County:</strong> Thousand Oaks, Simi Valley, Oxnard, Ventura, Camarillo, Moorpark.</p>

